      "content": "thanks. so like, when they were talking about things like IQ or \"economic productivity,\" did they actually provide any specific \"data\" or physiological arguments they used to back that up? i want to show how they tried to make it look like hard science rather than just prejudice. like, what were the specific biological or evolutionary claims they made about why one group would be \"naturally\" more productive or smarter than another?",
